description:
This is a 21 minute workout called 'Lower Body Blast Circuit' from the channel Peter Donohoe.
The workout falls under Strength/Calisthenics.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
You'll need Rower and Weights for this workout.
The workout has a The Competitor and The Disciplined Grind vibe.
The The Competitor vibe means Gamified, leaderboard-driven, full-send energy. This is especially good for Those who need to chase a score or beat their own record. The The Disciplined Grind vibe means No excuses, no distractions, just execute. This is especially good for When you want pure focus and efficiency..
The technique difficulty is Beginner and Intermediate.
The effort required is Moderate.

Original workout description: Get ready to strengthen your legs and glutes with Pete in this 20-minute circuit workout. Start with a dynamic warm-up on the mat to activate your muscles and prepare your body for movement. With a pair of dumbbells, move through reverse lunges, kickstand RDLs, and goblet squats that will build lower body strength and endurance. Mix in bursts on the Hydrow to engage your core and boost your cardio. Filmed in Charlestonâ€™s historic Navy shipyard, this workout is perfect for those looking to challenge their limits while enjoying a scenic backdrop. Jump in and feel the burn!
